
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Provider {
  - name: String
  - location: String
}

class Cruise {
  - cruiseNumber: String
  - cruiseName: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
  + addEmployee(employee: Employee): void
  + addGuest(guest: Guest): void
  + addShow(show: Show): void
  + addTicket(ticket: Ticket): void
}

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class Guest {
  - name: String
  - isVIP: Boolean
}

class Ship {
  - shipName: String
  - numberOfDecks: Integer
  - length: Double
  - passengerCapacity: Integer
}

class TravelAgency {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class Booking {
  - bookingNumber: String
  - bookingDate: Date
}

class DestinationArea {
  - areaName: String
  - seaName: String
}

class Show {
  - title: String
  - duration: Integer
}

class Ticket {
  - ticketId: String
  - guest: Guest
  - cruise: Cruise
}

class CruiseShipAssociation {
  - cruise: Cruise
  - ship: Ship
}

class CruiseDestination {
  - cruise: Cruise
  - destinationArea: DestinationArea
}

class GuestCruiseAssociation {
  - guest: Guest
  - cruise: Cruise
}

class CruiseBookingAssociation {
  - cruise: Cruise
  - booking: Booking
}

class GuestTicketAssociation {
  - guest: Guest
  - ticket: Ticket
}

class CruiseShowAssociation {
  - cruise: Cruise
  - show: Show
}

Provider "1" --> "0..*" Cruise
Cruise "1" --> "1" Ship : via CruiseShipAssociation
Cruise "1" --> "1" DestinationArea : via CruiseDestination
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Employee
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Show : via CruiseShowAssociation
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Ticket
Cruise "1" --> "0..*" Booking : via CruiseBookingAssociation
Guest "0..*" --> "0..*" Cruise : via GuestCruiseAssociation
Guest "1" --> "0..*" Ticket : via GuestTicketAssociation
Ticket "1" --> "1" Cruise
Booking "1" --> "1" Cruise
TravelAgency "1" --> "0..*" Booking
@enduml

### Explanation of Associations:
- A **Provider** organizes many **Cruises**.
- A **Cruise** uses exactly one **Ship** (via association class `CruiseShipAssociation`).
- A **Cruise** has a single **DestinationArea** (via `CruiseDestination`).
- A **Cruise** requires multiple **Employees**.
- A **Cruise** offers multiple **Shows** (via `CruiseShowAssociation`).
- A **Cruise** has multiple **Tickets**.
- A **Cruise** is booked through multiple **Bookings** (via `CruiseBookingAssociation`).
- A **Guest** can be part of multiple **Cruises** (via `GuestCruiseAssociation`).
- A **Guest** can have multiple **Tickets**, but only one per **Cruise** (via `GuestTicketAssociation`).
- A **Booking** is associated with a **TravelAgency**.
- A **Booking** is associated with a **Cruise**.

